oup stage and did not qualify for the 2014 FIFA World Cup. Their first match was against Scotland in FIFA World Cup in which they defeated 0-1 against Scotland. Their biggest win was 6-1 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/uruguay-road-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Uruguay</a> in 1986 FIFA World Cup and their biggest defeat was 1-5 against Spain in 1986 FIFA World Cup.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-714" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Denmark-300x191.jpeg" alt="" width="552" height="351" />

<strong><u>World Cup Qualifier Europe</u></strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The World Cup qualifier in Europe selects 14 countries for the FIFA World Cup and for 2018 FIFA World Cup; Russia qualifies for being a host country. 52 countries who are the members of FIFA from Europe go for the preliminary competition where those 5 countries were divided into 9 groups in which 7 groups contain 6 teams and rest of the two groups contain only 5 teams. <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/england-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">England</a>, <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/france-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">France</a>, <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/germany-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Germany</a>, Italy, Netherlands, and <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/spain-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spain</a> are placed in a group containing 6 teams. Winners from each group qualify automatically and the eight best runners-up go for the playoffs from which 4 teams are selected. Thus, in this way, the Europe qualifier selects 14 nations for the FIFA World Cup.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Denmark finished second in the Group E behind Poland with total 20 points along with Montenegro, Romania, Armenia, and Kazakhstan. Denmark managed to win 6 games out of total 10 games. They drew 2 matches and lost 2 matches in the qualifying round. They lost a match against Montenegro and <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/poland-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Poland</a>. After managed to finish second in the group,<a href="http://wikiceleb.com/poland-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Poland</a> was advance to the second group and faced against the Republic of Ireland. The Republic of Ireland lost 1-5against Denmark and they got qualified for the FIFA World Cup 2018. Denmark star Christian Eriksen scored a hat-trick against the Republic of Ireland leads his team to FIFA World Cup 2018.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-716" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Denmark-Goal-Celebration-1-300x180.jpg" alt="" width="542" height="325" />

